<p><a name="Viewpoints" id="Viewpoints"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Thomas_Friedman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: Viewpoints">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Viewpoints</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.slate.com/id/2062905/" class="external text" title="http://www.slate.com/id/2062905/" rel="nofollow">"Thomas Friedman: What makes the Timesman a great columnist? Not that peace proposal"</a> by <a href="/wiki/David_Plotz" title="David Plotz">David Plotz</a>, 2002</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dissidentvoice.org/Articles/Shirazi_Friedman.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.dissidentvoice.org/Articles/Shirazi_Friedman.htm" rel="nofollow">"The Quest for Symbols"</a> by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Said_Shirazi&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Said Shirazi (page does not exist)">Said Shirazi</a> - criticism of Friedman's writing, 2002</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nypress.com/16/46/news&amp;columns/cage.cfm" class="external text" title="http://www.nypress.com/16/46/news&amp;columns/cage.cfm" rel="nofollow">"Back at the Wheel: Thomas Friedman just loves to grind the gears"</a> A critique of Thomas Friedman's writing style by <a href="/wiki/Matt_Taibbi" title="Matt Taibbi">Matt Taibbi</a>, 2003</li>
<li><a href="http://zmagsite.zmag.org/Nov2003/herman1103.html" class="external text" title="http://zmagsite.zmag.org/Nov2003/herman1103.html" rel="nofollow">"The Geraldo Rivera of the New York Times"</a> - criticism by <a href="/wiki/Edward_S._Herman" title="Edward S. Herman">Edward S. Herman</a>, Z Magazine, November 2003</li>
<li><a href="http://www.thewoodenrobot.com/timesselect.html" class="external text" title="http://www.thewoodenrobot.com/timesselect.html" rel="nofollow">"Missing the Bus to Bangladesh"</a>, a parody of Friedman's writing style, 2005</li>
<li><a href="http://www.thenation.com/docprint.mhtml?i=20050829&amp;s=berman" class="external text" title="http://www.thenation.com/docprint.mhtml?i=20050829&amp;s=berman" rel="nofollow">"The Strategic Class"</a>, by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Ari_Berman&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Ari Berman (page does not exist)">Ari Berman</a>, 2005</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nypress.com/18/16/news&amp;columns/taibbi.cfm" class="external text" title="http://www.nypress.com/18/16/news&amp;columns/taibbi.cfm" rel="nofollow">"Flathead: The peculiar genius of Thomas L. Friedman"</a>, review of <i>The World is Flat</i> by <a href="/wiki/Matt_Taibbi" title="Matt Taibbi">Matt Taibbi</a>, 2005</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dailykos.com/story/2006/7/31/121447/985" class="external text" title="http://www.dailykos.com/story/2006/7/31/121447/985" rel="nofollow">"Billionaire Scion Tom Friedman"</a> by <a href="/wiki/David_Sirota" title="David Sirota">David Sirota</a>, 2006</li>
<li><a href="http://www.fair.org/index.php?page=2884" class="external text" title="http://www.fair.org/index.php?page=2884" rel="nofollow">Tom Friedman's Flexible Deadlines</a> A review of Friedman's punditry with respect to Iraq by FAIR</li>
<li><a href="http://www.observer.com/20061120/20061120_Tom_Scocca_media_offtherecord.asp" class="external text" title="http://www.observer.com/20061120/20061120_Tom_Scocca_media_offtherecord.asp" rel="nofollow">Not Since Nixon--Friedman in China, Sells Tom's World</a>, <i>The New York Observer</i></li>
</ul>


